sentence: Chiangmai is an attractive Thai house on Fayette Street in the heart of Conshohocken, PA. It is part of a three restaurant local chain that have a good reputation for authentic Thai cuisine in a nice atmosphere. My experience at lunch confirms that opinion. I entered about 1:00 PM and was seated at a deuce at the front window. Cool view of a bustling Fayette Street. The menu was presented by an attractive server who directed me to the specials page offering a prix fixe of soup, salad/app and entrée for $9.95. Sounded good, but I knew I couldn't eat that much, so ordered the Vegetarian Drunken Noodles. While waiting, I took in the décor of the dining room. It was simple, yet beautifully appointed with wall and ceiling hangings from home. Lots of color and texture. The staff was likewise adorned in native dress. It wasn't difficult to remember my days relaxing in Chaingmai after business in Bangkok. Brought a secret smile to my face. The large platter arrived quickly - a massive load of broad noodles, chopped broccoli, carrots, onions, sprouts and cubes of tofu in a moderately spicy sauce. Really flavorful and good mix of textures, shapes
